Build a modern, modular e-commerce site template using the following stack and structure. The goal is to provide a reusable, production-ready foundation for any online store using Next.js, Supabase, and optional BigCommerce integration.

## Framework

-   Next.js 14+ using the App Router
-   React 18 with Server Components and Streaming where applicable
-   File-based routing via `app/` directory

## Styling

-   Tailwind CSS (configured)
-   shadcn/ui for accessible UI components
-   Prettier + ESLint for formatting and linting

## Backend (Headless)

-   Supabase for:
    -   Product/category data
    -   Contact form storage
    -   Auth (email/password or magic link)
-   BigCommerce (optional):
    -   Product/category fetching via Storefront GraphQL API
    -   No cart/checkout integration needed for now
    -   Abstract service layer so itâ€™s swappable with Supabase

## Pages

-   Home with featured products
-   Category browsing
-   Product detail page
-   Contact page (writes to Supabase, sends via Resend)
-   Admin dashboard scaffold (non-functional UI shell)

## Integrations

-   Resend for contact form notifications
-   Supabase Auth
-   API routes using `app/api/`

## Tooling

-   TypeScript
-   ESLint + Prettier
-   Tailwind via PostCSS
-   `env.local.example` for API keys and setup

## Deployment

-   Should work on Render, DigitalOcean App Platform, or similar
-   No reliance on Vercel-specific APIs or hosting behaviors
